Law enforcement searched the local area with a cadaver dog and found skeletal remains without a skull, on 3/13/07. Estimation of race is uncertain.  Analysis indicates an Asian/American Indian or Hispanic origin.  The recovered hair is consistent with African American.

The chest, abdomen, and the right and left upper and lower extremities are mostly skeletonized. The head, neck, chest, ribs, spine and pelvis are relatively intact. 

Detached from the body are the right femur with some dried and moist soft tissues
